recalls.Component: SERVICE BRAKES, HYDRAULIC:FOUNDATION COMPONENTS:HOSES, LINES/PIPING, AND FITTINGS
recalls.Summary: General Motors LLC (GM) is recalling certain model year 2004-2007 Cadillac CTS-V vehicles manufactured between September 6, 2003, and June 11, 2007, currently registered, or originally sold, in Connecticut, Delaware, Illinois, Indiana, Iowa, Maine, Maryland, Massachusetts, Michigan, Minnesota, Missouri, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Ohio, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, Vermont, West Virginia, Wisconsin and the District of Columbia.  In the affected vehicles, snow or water containing road salt or other contaminants may corrode the front brake hose fitting at the caliper.
recalls.Consequence: Corrosion may cause the brake system to leak which could lengthen the distance needed to stop the vehicle and increase the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: GM will notify owners, and dealers will replace both front brake hose assemblies, free of charge. The recall began on May 8, 2015.  Owners may contact Cadillac customer service at 1-800-458-8006. GM's number for this recall is 15149.  Note: This recall is an expansion of recall 10V-105.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

issues.title: Differential Failure
issues.description: The rear differential in Gen 1 CTS-V models is prone to failure, particularly under aggressive driving conditions. The differential can experience bearing wear, gear damage, or complete failure.
symptoms: Loss of power to rear wheels
issues.fix_description: Replace differential assembly or rebuild with upgraded components
issues.prevention: Regular differential fluid changes, avoid aggressive launches

issues.title: Transmission Overheating
issues.description: The 6L80E automatic transmission can overheat during aggressive driving or track use, leading to fluid breakdown and internal damage.
issues.fix_description: Install transmission cooler, rebuild transmission if damaged
issues.prevention: Add aftermarket transmission cooler, regular fluid changes

issues.title: Throttle Body Carbon Buildup
issues.description: The LS6 engine's throttle body accumulates carbon deposits over time, causing rough idle and reduced performance.
issues.fix_description: Clean throttle body with appropriate cleaner, reset idle learn procedure
issues.prevention: Use quality fuel, periodic throttle body cleaning

issues.title: Rear Shock Mount Failure
issues.description: The rear shock mounts can crack or fail, particularly on vehicles used for track driving or aggressive street use.
issues.fix_description: Weld reinforcement plates or replace shock tower assembly
issues.prevention: Avoid excessive compression loading, inspect regularly

issues.title: Fuel Pump Failure
issues.description: The high-pressure fuel pump can fail, particularly in higher mileage vehicles, causing fuel starvation and engine performance issues.
symptoms: Engine cutting out at highway speeds
issues.fix_description: Replace fuel pump assembly and fuel filter
issues.prevention: Keep fuel tank above 1/4 full, use quality fuel

issues.title: Window Regulator Failure
issues.description: Power window regulators, particularly on the driver's side, can fail causing windows to drop or become inoperable.
issues.fix_description: Replace window regulator motor and mechanism
issues.prevention: Lubricate window tracks, avoid forcing stuck windows

issues.title: Brake Pad Wear and Rotor Warping
issues.description: High-performance Brembo brakes wear quickly and rotors can warp under aggressive use, leading to pedal pulsation and reduced braking performance.
issues.fix_description: Replace brake pads and resurface or replace rotors
issues.prevention: Proper brake cooling, quality brake pads, avoid overheating

issues.title: Cooling System Issues
issues.description: Radiator and cooling system components can fail, particularly the plastic end tanks on radiators, leading to overheating issues.
issues.fix_description: Replace radiator, water pump, or cooling system components as needed
issues.prevention: Regular coolant changes, inspect for leaks

issues.title: Suspension Bushings Deterioration
issues.description: Control arm bushings and other suspension bushings deteriorate over time, affecting handling and causing noise.
issues.fix_description: Replace worn bushings with OEM or upgraded polyurethane units

issues.title: Engine Oil Consumption
issues.description: Some LS6 engines experience higher than normal oil consumption, particularly at higher mileages, due to valve guide wear or ring issues.
issues.fix_description: Engine rebuild or replacement depending on severity
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes with quality oil, avoid overheating

editorial.hero_blurb: The first-generation CTS-V announced Cadillac's shocking return to performance credibility. This wasn't just another luxury sedan with more power—it was a legitimate BMW M5 and Mercedes E55 AMG competitor that could actually deliver on its promises.
editorial.essence: The CTS-V Gen 1 represented Cadillac's bold reentry into high-performance luxury, combining Corvette powertrains with Germanic chassis tuning. It proved American luxury could be sophisticated and brutally fast simultaneously, establishing the V-Series as a force to be reckoned with.
editorial.heritage: Born from Cadillac's desperate need to compete with European super sedans, the CTS-V borrowed heavily from the Corvette parts bin while receiving chassis development from renowned British firm Lotus. This collaboration created America's first credible answer to BMW's M division.
editorial.design_philosophy: Engineers prioritized balanced performance over straight-line speed, creating a sedan that could carve corners as confidently as it conquered highways. The goal was European sophistication with American muscle—no compromises.
editorial.motorsport_history: The CTS-V proved its mettle in SCCA World Challenge and various amateur racing series, with privateers finding success in both sedan racing and track day events. Its motorsport DNA was legitimate, not just marketing fluff.
editorial.engine_character: The LS6 and LS2 V8s deliver intoxicating American muscle character—smooth, torquey, and eager to rev. Power builds linearly with a satisfying surge past 4000 RPM, accompanied by that unmistakable LS rumble that makes every drive feel special.
editorial.transmission_feel: The Tremec T56 six-speed manual offers precise, mechanical engagement with short throws and a perfectly weighted clutch. Each gear change feels purposeful and connected, enhancing the driver's bond with the machine.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Lotus-tuned suspension delivers remarkable balance between comfort and capability. The chassis feels planted and predictable, with controlled body motions that inspire confidence while maintaining reasonable ride quality for daily use.
editorial.steering_feel: Hydraulic power steering provides excellent feedback and natural weighting that loads up progressively in corners. Turn-in is sharp without being nervous, and the steering communicates road surface changes clearly to the driver.
editorial.brake_confidence: Brembo four-piston brakes deliver strong, consistent stopping power with excellent pedal feel. Initial bite is firm but progressive, and fade resistance is impressive even during spirited driving sessions.
editorial.sound_signature: The exhaust note is pure American V8 theater—a deep, muscular rumble at idle that builds to an aggressive roar under acceleration. The sound is intoxicating without being antisocial, perfectly matching the car's character.
editorial.ideal_owner: Performance-oriented drivers who appreciate American muscle wrapped in European sophistication. Perfect for enthusiasts who want M5 performance without the BMW maintenance costs and complexity.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Buyers seeking ultimate refinement, those prioritizing fuel economy, or drivers who prefer understated luxury without the aggressive performance edge.
editorial.buyers_summary: Look for well-maintained examples with service records, as these engines are bulletproof when properly cared for. The manual transmission is highly desirable and adds significant value to any CTS-V purchase.
pros: Genuine track capability with daily usability
